Rating: 3
These are nice and tasty. I took others advice and use 1.5 C flour. Perfect. For fun, once some batter is in the mold, stick a little chunk of dark chocolate. Cook same length of time. Cool, then serve with a scoop of mint choco chip ice cream. Oh heaven.

Rating: 4
These came out very well. Only difference, I used the zest of two oranges instead of lemons and used 1.5 cups of flour instead of the 1.75 cups in the recipe. Baked for 15 minutes. And made about 30 cookies. Very fluffy, cakey feel. Wonderful with a nice cup of tea and milk.

