Absolutely wonderful. All the proportions in the recipe are perfect. I have been making these over and over again, and they barely last a day. Try dipping them in tea or coffee.

Rating: 4
I was very pleased with this recipe, but found that the Madeleines became more dense than I like once cooled. I therefore reduced the flour to 1 1/2 cups, and substituted cake flour for regular flour. Additionally, they were too sweet for my taste, so I reduced the sugar, and lemon zest, by about half, and added a half-teaspoon of salt.

Rating: 4
